textBeforeTable: Personal: Daughter of Milton Daniels and Doris Law ... Born Nov. 15, 1989 ... Majoring in exercise science ... Meesha is her nickname ... Lists LeBron James of the Miami Heat as her favorite athlete ... Chose Georgia College because it was close to home ... Enjoys extra sleep in her free time ... Has cookies for her pre-game ritual ... Lists Law Abiding Citizen as her favorite movie ... Her ringtone is beep beep bop.  High School: Was a graduate of Cedar Shoals ... Two-time Northeast Georgia Team of the Year ... Elected to All-Region team ... Was also on the North All-Star team ... Had 810 career points ... 2007 MVP of the Swee South Classic at Morgan County High School ... Was team’s leading rebounder and scorer. 2008-09: Played in 21 games ... Averaged 1.0 points and 1.3 rebounds per contest with six blocks ... Averages bumped to 1.1 points and 1.4 rebounds in PBC games, with all six blocks ... Notched her first career points in the win over Newberry Dec. 30 ... Netted career-highs with six points against Armstrong Atlantic Jan. 14 and seven rebounds in the loss at Francis Marion Jan. 17 ...
